flash.tools.debugger

Interface ValueAttribute


  • public interface ValueAttribute
    Author:
    mmorearty

    • Field Summary

      Fields 
      Modifier and Type Field and Description
      static int IS_CLASS
      Indicates that an object is actually a Class.
      static int IS_EXCEPTION
      Indicates that the value that has been returned for a variable is actually not its real value; instead, it is the message of an exception that was thrown while executing the getter for the variable.

    • Field Detail

      • IS_EXCEPTION

        static final int IS_EXCEPTION
        Indicates that the value that has been returned for a variable is actually not its real value; instead, it is the message of an exception that was thrown while executing the getter for the variable.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • IS_CLASS

        static final int IS_CLASS
        Indicates that an object is actually a Class. For example, if you have 
            var someClass:Class = Button;
        ... then someClass will have IS_CLASS set to true.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values
